headline: Why Centene (CNC) May Need to Rethink Medicare Advantage Strategy After Minimal CMS Rate Proposal
summary: Earlier this week, the Centers for Medicare & Medicaid Services proposed a 0.09% payment rate increase and tighter risk‑adjustment rules for 2027 Medicare Advantage plans, a much smaller change than industry participants had anticipated and with potentially meaningful effects on government-sponsored health plan providers such as Centene. Because risk‑adjustment rules directly influence how insurers are paid for caring for higher-cost patients, the proposal raises fresh questions about how...

headline: Is It Time To Reassess Centene (CNC) After Prolonged Share Price Weakness?
summary: If you are wondering whether Centene's current share price reflects its true worth, you are not alone. This article walks through what the numbers say about value. headline: WellCare of Kentucky and Centene Foundation Give $145,000 to Food Pantries to Help Tackle Food Insecurity in Kentucky
summary: WellCare of Kentucky and Centene Foundation, the philanthropic arm of Centene Corporation (NYSE: CNC), today announced a strategic and timely investment aimed at addressing food insecurity across Kentucky. According to Feeding America, food insecurity has reached historic highs in Kentucky, with nearly 280,000 people (18.2%) facing hunger, the largest number ever recorded.
